The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 29 July is 56,128 (6,496.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 24 July, there were 2,853 new confirmed cases (330.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 17 July, there were 4,219 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 32% (1,366 fewer cases).
